keyInstructions.setupInfo:
To use the Google AI SDK, you need to obtain an API key from the Google Cloud Console.

1. Sign up for a Google Cloud account at https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/credentials
2. Once you have an account, navigate to your credentials page to find your API key
3. Store your API key securely and never share it publicly

To use the SDK:

1. Install the package: `npm install @microfox/ai-provider-google`
2. Import and initialize the SDK:

```typescript
import { createGoogleAiProvider } from '@microfox/ai-provider-google';

const provider = createGoogleAiProvider({
  apiKey: 'YOUR_API_KEY_HERE'
});
```

3. You can now use the SDK methods to interact with the Google AI API:

```typescript
const response = await provider.generateText({ model: 'gemini-pro', prompt: 'Hello, world!' });
console.log(response);
```

Environment Variables:
You can also use an environment variable to store your API key. Set the `GOOGLE_API_KEY` environment variable, and the SDK will automatically use it if no API key is provided during initialization.

